685
00:35:19,882 --> 00:35:21,043
会不停地强调假话一样
you overplay it?

686
00:35:21,184 --> 00:35:22,913
她总是不停地说
She had gone on and on

687
00:35:23,053 --> 00:35:25,419
萨拉是红头发这事太奇怪了
about how weird it is that Sarah has red hair.

688
00:35:25,555 --> 00:35:26,715
『太怪了！』
"It's so odd!

689
00:35:26,856 --> 00:35:29,791
『可能是我堂妹玛格丽特安妮是红发的关系吧』
"I guess my cousin Margaret-Anne has red hair. "

690
00:35:29,926 --> 00:35:31,153
这事突然就闪回到我的脑海中
And that struck me,

691
00:35:31,293 --> 00:35:32,590
接着我看见他一头红发的照片
and then I saw him with the red hair,

692
00:35:32,728 --> 00:35:34,128
所以我想...
and I really did think...

693
00:35:34,264 --> 00:35:35,892
我当时真的觉得这是真的
I really thought it was true.

694
00:35:37,500 --> 00:35:40,163
有时候 我真的开始相信那是真的
So at some point, I think I did start to believe it was true

695
00:35:40,304 --> 00:35:42,829
开始想是不是该有人把真相告诉你
and thought someone should say something to you.

696
00:35:42,974 --> 00:35:45,964
我记得我们几个人凑在一起讨论过
I feel like we all had a discussion about it at some point,

697
00:35:46,109 --> 00:35:47,941
当然 不包括你
"we all" being everyone but you.

698
00:35:48,079 --> 00:35:49,774
约翰尼说我是个大嘴巴
And I think Johnny said I had a big mouth

699
00:35:49,914 --> 00:35:51,973
我可能会把这事告诉你
and that I was probably gonna tell you or something.

700
00:35:52,116 --> 00:35:54,108
我和他说『我觉得我们应该告诉她』
And I was saying,"I think we should tell her. "

701
00:35:55,620 --> 00:35:57,452
现在 让我们把时间向前推进一点
Now, I think we should leap forward to a point

702
00:35:57,589 --> 00:35:59,819
在黛安去世几年后
several years after Diane's death,

703
00:36:00,558 --> 00:36:03,722
晚餐桌上的那个陈年笑话
when the jokes with her family round the dinner table

704
00:36:03,862 --> 00:36:05,294
似乎也不再好笑了
were not so funny,

705
00:36:05,996 --> 00:36:07,158
当话题开始变得严肃
and since it went further

706
00:36:07,300 --> 00:36:09,393
而多伦多剧团里那个可能的父亲
and named the member of the cast of Toronto

707
00:36:09,535 --> 00:36:11,696
身份正日渐明朗
who was her possible parent,

708
00:36:11,838 --> 00:36:15,433
她觉得是时候迈出关键一步了
she decided it was time to take the plunge.

709
00:36:15,576 --> 00:36:17,974
她打电话给杰弗 问他可不可以见面
She phoned Geoff and asked if they could meet.

710
00:36:19,578 --> 00:36:20,637
你打电话来...
You called...

711
00:36:22,014 --> 00:36:25,246
我们安排了见面
and we arranged to meet,

712
00:36:25,386 --> 00:36:28,253
你问我当年在蒙特利尔发生的事
and you wanted to know about that time in Montreal.

713
00:36:28,389 --> 00:36:30,358
我当时把手搭在你的肩上 心想
I remember putting my arm around you,and I thought,

714
00:36:30,492 --> 00:36:32,288
『哦 天啊 希望我没做得太过』
"Oh, boy, I hope that isn't too forward or something. "

715
00:36:32,426 --> 00:36:35,589
我开始想起你问我的那些事
And I remember recounting some of the same tales.

716
00:36:35,729 --> 00:36:38,061
那些我遗忘了很久的关于黛安的事
I hadn't really thought about Diane for a long time,

717
00:36:38,198 --> 00:36:40,929
我当时心里挺难过的
so I recall being pretty sad.

718
00:36:41,736 --> 00:36:45,297
从我18岁起 就总有人说
So, since I was 18, there was this rumor

719
00:36:45,440 --> 00:36:47,567
你是我的亲生父亲
that you were my biological father.

720
00:36:49,310 --> 00:36:50,607
这事听起来是不是很奇怪
It's been this bizarre thing.

721
00:36:50,745 --> 00:36:54,113
我总在想 到底是从什么地方传开的
It's like, how that rumor began,where did it come from?

722
00:36:54,250 --> 00:36:55,808
所以我就想问你一下
And I just wanted to ask you about that.

723
00:36:55,951 --> 00:36:58,920
你和我妈在交往过程中发生过『那种』事情吗
Was there ever anything romantic in your relationship with Mom,

724
00:36:59,054 --> 00:37:01,420
还是说你们只是普通朋友
or was it always just friendship?

725
00:37:03,393 --> 00:37:04,723
我们只是普通朋友
Uh, it was friendship.

726
00:37:06,494 --> 00:37:08,760
我还记得你说...
I remember you saying...

727
00:37:08,899 --> 00:37:11,527
你说那句话时我很惊讶
being surprised at you saying,

728
00:37:11,668 --> 00:37:15,934
『我们家里的每个人都知道』
"It's common knowledge in my family that, uh, my...

729
00:37:16,072 --> 00:37:18,063
『我妈当时爱上你了』
"that my mom was in love with you. "

730
00:37:18,208 --> 00:37:20,733
我当时很吃惊
And I was taken aback at that.

731
00:37:23,447 --> 00:37:24,573
我觉得有点触动
I was touched.

732
00:37:32,390 --> 00:37:34,916
杰弗坚持说
Everything Geoff said suggested he was certain

733
00:37:35,060 --> 00:37:38,119
黛安没有对迈克尔不忠
that Diane had stayed faithful to Michael.

734
00:37:39,329 --> 00:37:43,097
但她脑中的疑问之种仍在生长
But that seed of doubt had grown even larger in her mind.

735
00:37:43,936 --> 00:37:47,428
她觉得他是一个可爱 坦诚 慷慨的人
She thought he was a lovely,open,and generous person,

736
00:37:48,240 --> 00:37:50,869
但她也觉得他藏着秘密
and yet she felt he was hiding something.

737
00:37:51,577 --> 00:37:55,412
但她又一次放开了追问的那条线
But, once again, she let the story lie.

738
00:37:55,548 --> 00:37:58,210
这个谜团仍然没能解开
And so the conundrum remained just that.

739
00:37:59,052 --> 00:38:03,251
一天 她在多伦多偶然遇见一位蒙特利尔的制作人
One day, she chanced to meet a Montreal producer in Toronto

740
00:38:03,390 --> 00:38:07,189
提到自己要去蒙特利尔几天
and mentions that she's going to Montreal in a couple of days,

741
00:38:07,327 --> 00:38:10,229
那位制作人说『你到蒙特利尔以后』
and the producer says, "While you're there,

742
00:38:10,364 --> 00:38:13,162
『可以和哈利·高金见个面』
"you might want to meet up with Harry Gulkin.

743
00:38:13,300 --> 00:38:15,200
『他也是位电影制作人』
"He's an important film producer

744
00:38:15,336 --> 00:38:17,930
『在你母亲做选角导演时与她合作过』
"that your mother worked with as a casting director

745
00:38:18,072 --> 00:38:21,702
『或许可以帮助你了解下你母亲的事』
"and can probably tell you more about your mother in those days. "

746
00:38:21,843 --> 00:38:23,538
萨拉很高兴
And Sarah is very pleased.

747
00:38:23,678 --> 00:38:24,803
对自己出生前母亲的生活
She always likes to hear

748
00:38:24,945 --> 00:38:27,574
她总是充满好奇
about her mother's life before Sarah's birth,

749
00:38:27,716 --> 00:38:29,877
同时她也觉得
and she also realized that this Harry

750
00:38:30,018 --> 00:38:31,679
哈利可能
may be able to shed more light

751
00:38:31,820 --> 00:38:34,880
会对母亲是否和当时的剧组成员有外遇一事
on the possibility of her mother having had an affair

752
00:38:35,023 --> 00:38:36,321
略知一二
with a member of the cast.

753
00:38:36,459 --> 00:38:38,517
所以她拨了哈利的电话
And so she phones Harry

754
00:38:38,660 --> 00:38:42,098
问他是否愿意和自己聊聊
and asks if she could get together with him for a chat.

755
00:38:42,232 --> 00:38:43,926
嗨 萨拉 谢谢你主动与我联系
Hi, Sarah,and a warm welcome.

756
00:38:44,599 --> 00:38:47,068
艾妮说你想见我
Arnie Gelbart told me you would like to see me.

757
00:38:47,203 --> 00:38:49,434
正好我也想见你
That's good,because I would love to see you.

758
00:38:49,573 --> 00:38:51,938
今天下午我会在办公室
I can be reached in my office this afternoon,

759
00:38:52,074 --> 00:38:53,405
或者你可以在白天时发邮件给我
or email me here during the day.

760
00:38:53,543 --> 00:38:54,875
嗨 哈利 
Hi, Harry.Great to hear from you.

761
00:38:55,012 --> 00:38:58,140
我一直记得我妈总是用仰慕的语气谈论你
I always remember my mom talking about you with such affection.

762
00:38:58,282 --> 00:38:59,944
很高兴终于能和你见面
It'd be great to finally meet you.

763
00:39:00,083 --> 00:39:02,950
下午3：45有空到Ex-Centris外喝杯咖啡么
Would you be free at 3:45 to meet at Ex-Centris for a coffee?

764
00:39:03,086 --> 00:39:04,145
他同意了
He agrees,

765
00:39:04,288 --> 00:39:06,950
几天后 他们在一家餐馆见了面
and a couple of days later,they meet in a restaurant.

766
00:39:07,090 --> 00:39:08,854
接下来发生的事
What happens next is what I can remember

767
00:39:08,993 --> 00:39:11,722
我只能回忆起与萨拉有关的部分
of Sarah's relating the event.

768
00:39:22,107 --> 00:39:24,132
你说你一直很想见我
and you said that you had wanted to meet me

769
00:39:24,276 --> 00:39:28,043
因为你的母亲常常提到我
because your mother had talked about me a lot.

770
00:39:28,915 --> 00:39:31,748
接着我们又聊了很多
And then we talked about a million things.

771
00:39:31,885 --> 00:39:35,149
你说你十五岁时不得不退学
You told me how you had quit school at 15,

772
00:39:35,287 --> 00:39:37,256
最主要的一个原因是
and that one of the dominating reasons

773
00:39:37,390 --> 00:39:38,856
你当时的政治立场
was your politics at the time

774
00:39:38,991 --> 00:39:41,358
以及你打算加入阶级斗争军的行列
and your desire to join the class struggle.

775
00:39:41,494 --> 00:39:42,961
我觉得这很有意思
That struck me as very interesting,

776
00:39:43,096 --> 00:39:44,825
因为我曾经做过一模一样的事
because I had done exactly the same thing.

777
00:39:44,965 --> 00:39:48,265
在那次谈话后 我们的关系变得很好
And we became very close during that conversation.

778
00:39:48,402 --> 00:39:50,802
我们在彼此身上找到了许多共同点
We found a whole number of things in common

779
00:39:50,938 --> 00:39:54,373
情感 反应 回应他人的方式
in terms of feelings, reactions, response.

780
00:39:54,508 --> 00:39:55,941
我记得你说 第一眼见到他
And I remember you saying,as soon as you met him,

781
00:39:56,077 --> 00:39:58,408
就觉得有种莫名的安定感
you felt at ease with him in a certain way,

782
00:39:58,545 --> 00:40:00,515
也正是因为这种安定感
and because you felt so at ease with him,

783
00:40:00,649 --> 00:40:02,674
让你决定问他是否知道
you had decided to ask him if he knew anything

784
00:40:02,818 --> 00:40:06,844
杰弗·博斯是你生父这一说法的真实性
about this rumor about Geoff Bowes being your dad.

785
00:40:07,755 --> 00:40:10,589
你问他『你有没有听说过』
You asked him the question,"Have you ever heard anything

786
00:40:10,726 --> 00:40:13,889
『我妈在蒙特利尔演出时有了外遇』
"about my mom having had an affair while she was in Montreal?"

787
00:40:14,029 --> 00:40:15,088
你抬起头来对我说
You looked up and you said,

788
00:40:15,231 --> 00:40:17,495
『你觉得是杰弗·博斯么？』
"Do you think it was Geoff Bowes?"

789
00:40:18,401 --> 00:40:19,891
我说『不』
So I said, "No. "

790
00:40:20,637 --> 00:40:22,832
你又说『那你知道是谁么？』
She said, "Do you know who it was?"

791
00:40:22,972 --> 00:40:24,303
我说『我知道』
And I said, "Yes. "

792
00:40:24,439 --> 00:40:26,737
『我知道杰弗·博斯不是你父亲』
"No, I know that Geoff Bowes isn't your dad. "

793
00:40:26,875 --> 00:40:27,865
你说『你怎么知道？』
And you said, "How do you know that?"

794
00:40:28,011 --> 00:40:29,410
他说『因为我才是你父亲』
And he said, "Cause I'm your dad. "

795
00:40:30,681 --> 00:40:34,549
他说『可能 而非也许』
He said,"It's possible, not probable. "

796
00:40:34,685 --> 00:40:36,517
你在电话里就是这么和我说的吧
I think those were the exact words you said to me on the phone.

797
00:40:36,655 --> 00:40:37,678
是么
Were they?

798
00:40:37,821 --> 00:40:41,051
他说『我以为你是因为这个才来找我的』
He said, "I thought that's why you wanted to speak to me,

799
00:40:41,191 --> 00:40:44,682
『因为你妈妈和我之间的事』
"because your mom and I had an affair. "

800
00:40:44,827 --> 00:40:48,492
『事实上 她是和我外遇了』
"In fact, she had an affair with me. "

801
00:40:48,633 --> 00:40:50,328
我说『是我』
And I said, "Me. "

802
00:40:55,240 --> 00:40:56,867
你愣了一下
So you stopped for a moment,

803
00:40:57,008 --> 00:40:59,441
又说『你现在还这么觉得么』
then you said, "Do you still think so?"

804
00:40:59,576 --> 00:41:01,409
我说『在和你聊天...』
And I said, "After talking to you

805
00:41:01,547 --> 00:41:04,710
『近距离看着你将近三小时之后 我可以确定』
"and looking at you for close to three hours, yes. "

806
00:41:04,850 --> 00:41:06,215
我说『你觉得呢？』
I said, "What do you think?"

807
00:41:06,352 --> 00:41:09,754
而你说『嗯 我也觉得是这样』
And you said, "Yeah, I think so, too. "

808
00:41:09,890 --> 00:41:11,856
萨拉哑口无言
Sarah is speechless.

809
00:41:12,957 --> 00:41:16,086
他本想知道更多关于杰弗的事
She's come all this way to find out about Geoff,

810
00:41:17,097 --> 00:41:19,565
却意外地和母亲的情人共处了一下午
and now she's sitting with her mother's lover.

811
00:41:28,308 --> 00:41:32,210
那是1978年2月底的事了
It was late February of 1978.

812
00:41:32,346 --> 00:41:34,746
我当时心情有些沮丧
I was sort of mildly depressed...

813
00:41:34,882 --> 00:41:37,283
隆冬时节 无所事事 孤身一人
midwinter, nothing to do,living alone...

814
00:41:38,019 --> 00:41:40,783
我就决定去中央剧院看戏
and I decided to go to the Centaur Theatre

815
00:41:40,922 --> 00:41:44,379
大卫·费那里奥的新剧正在公演
to see the latest production of David Fennario.

816
00:41:44,524 --> 00:41:46,823
我刚进去不久
So I went down there,and after a minute,

817
00:41:46,961 --> 00:41:48,361
演员们就登台了
as the cast came on stage,

818
00:41:48,497 --> 00:41:52,866
出现在眼前的一位女士让我呆住了
I was transfixed by this glorious lady who was on stage.

819
00:41:53,001 --> 00:41:54,468
是完全被迷住了
Really just bowled over.

820
00:41:54,603 --> 00:41:58,562
戏落幕的时候 我仍然觉得很害羞
When the play was over,I still had certain reserves of shyness,

821
00:41:58,707 --> 00:42:00,105
从头到尾我都在害羞
which still remain,

822
00:42:00,241 --> 00:42:02,472
所以我没有去后台
so I didn't go backstage,

823
00:42:02,612 --> 00:42:04,408
而是打算睡前
and I decided to have a nightcap

824
00:42:04,546 --> 00:42:08,142
去那家『三驾马车』小酒馆喝一杯
at what I considered then my geriatric bar, the Troika.

825
00:42:08,284 --> 00:42:09,216
我点了杯饮料
I ordered a drink,

826
00:42:09,352 --> 00:42:11,115
酒吧里放着伤感的俄罗斯三重奏
and they had a schmaltzy Russian trio,

827
00:42:11,254 --> 00:42:12,778
五分钟后
and after about five minutes,

828
00:42:12,922 --> 00:42:15,448
刚才舞台上的那位女士
who walks in but this lady who had been on stage

829
00:42:15,593 --> 00:42:16,786
和其它剧组演员一起走了进来
with some other cast members,

830
00:42:16,926 --> 00:42:18,655
我心想『哦 上帝啊』
so I figure, "Oh, my God,"

831
00:42:18,795 --> 00:42:21,765
我便起身混进了那群人当中
and I sort of sidled into the middle of the group,

832
00:42:21,899 --> 00:42:23,595
不时地开口
and I was able to inveigle myself

833
00:42:23,735 --> 00:42:25,793
插上一两句话
into the conversation to some degree,

834
00:42:25,936 --> 00:42:29,304
我试图找到和黛安单独说话的机会
and I did try to separate Diane from the group.

835
00:42:29,441 --> 00:42:31,533
但一小时后 我放弃了尝试
But after about an hour, it really was hopeless.

836
00:42:31,675 --> 00:42:33,803
这种事不会发生的
It wasn't gonna happen.

837
00:42:35,947 --> 00:42:37,643
黛安离开『三驾马车』的时候
When Diane left the Troika,

838
00:42:37,783 --> 00:42:39,648
我跟上了那一群人
I walked with them and with her,

839
00:42:39,785 --> 00:42:43,483
我问黛安是否能单独说句话
and I was trying again to separate Diane,

840
00:42:43,623 --> 00:42:44,646
她的回答是『不』
and she said, "No,

841
00:42:44,790 --> 00:42:46,587
『不过我们可以明晚再见』
"but we can meet tomorrow night. "

842
00:42:46,725 --> 00:42:50,218
在剧组留在蒙特利尔演出的剩下的日子里
We met every night after that for the remainder of the run,

843
00:42:50,363 --> 00:42:53,799
我们每天晚上都会见面 感觉彼此被对方强烈地吸引
and there was a very strong mutual attraction...

844
00:42:53,933 --> 00:42:55,560
那种感觉非常 非常强烈
very, very powerful thing.

845
00:42:56,837 --> 00:42:59,430
哈利每天都会等在楼梯下面
Harry would be down at the bottom of the stairs,

846
00:42:59,572 --> 00:43:00,630
我们都呆在剧院二层
we were in the upstairs theater,

847
00:43:00,773 --> 00:43:02,105
化妆间也在那上面
and our dressing room was up there,

848
00:43:02,242 --> 00:43:04,733
