and it made me think of stage-door Johnnies

849
00:43:04,878 --> 00:43:07,312
守在剧场外的狂热粉丝
from those old Broadway movies.

850
00:43:07,447 --> 00:43:09,745
我记得他有次问我『黛安在上面吗？』
I remember once he asked,"Is Diane there?

851
00:43:09,883 --> 00:43:11,282
『可以麻烦你上去和她说我来了吗？』
"Could you go and tell her that I'm here?"

852
00:43:11,418 --> 00:43:13,545
然后我就上楼说『哈利来啦』
And, you know, bound back upstairs,say, "Harry's here. "

853
00:43:13,687 --> 00:43:15,349
她说『好』 然后就一溜烟跑下去了
"Okay," and then run back down the stairs.

854
00:43:15,490 --> 00:43:16,889
我就喊『她下去啦！』
"She's coming. "

855
00:43:17,025 --> 00:43:20,928
哈利对她的热情相当炽烈
Harry developed this great,grand passion for her,

856
00:43:21,063 --> 00:43:24,088
他有一次对我说
and I think of Harry turning to me and saying,

857
00:43:24,233 --> 00:43:25,358
『她是不是很完美？』
"Isn't she wonderful?

858
00:43:25,500 --> 00:43:26,694
『是不是很有魅力？』
"Isn't she amazing?"

859
00:43:26,835 --> 00:43:29,600
我觉得这太有意思了
And I just found this highly amusing,

860
00:43:29,738 --> 00:43:35,575
他是一个相当精明 工于世故的男人
because I understood that he was a super-smart, sophisticated man

861
00:43:35,712 --> 00:43:37,612
对电影圈的一切了如指掌
with all kinds of connections to the film business,

862
00:43:37,747 --> 00:43:40,806
但他和我谈话的话题却总是关于
but his main topic of conversation with me

863
00:43:40,950 --> 00:43:43,181
黛安有多么完美
was the wonderfulness of Diane.

864
00:43:43,320 --> 00:43:45,184
这一点我是赞同的...
Which was...I agreed with him,

865
00:43:45,321 --> 00:43:49,554
但这些话在听过几次之后自然就腻了
but it becomes thin in terms of conversation material after a while.

866
00:43:49,693 --> 00:43:52,629
当你这样爱一个人的时候 你会变得极度自私
When you're in love like that,you become utterly selfish.

867
00:43:54,532 --> 00:43:57,898
他人的感受不再重要
Nothing that's happening to anyone else matters at all

868
00:43:58,034 --> 00:44:00,468
或者说 你不会再考虑他人的感受
or is a matter of any consideration.

869
00:44:00,604 --> 00:44:03,005
你变成了一只野兽
You just end up sort of

870
00:44:04,774 --> 00:44:07,370
专注 霸道
focused, intense,

871
00:44:07,512 --> 00:44:11,572
只想吞下爱情的猎物
and just wanting to consume the object of your love,

872
00:44:11,716 --> 00:44:15,152
周围的一切仿佛都不复存在
and nothing else exists.

873
00:44:16,889 --> 00:44:19,356
在他们排练的时候 我来探班过一次
I visited once during the rehearsal period,

874
00:44:19,490 --> 00:44:22,086
首演当夜我也在场
and then I think I went up for the opening night.

875
00:44:22,228 --> 00:44:24,219
我想哈利当时应该也在那里
I guess Harry would have been there.

876
00:44:24,364 --> 00:44:26,992
但他那天没有和她上床 因为那天和她上床的是我
But he wasn't sleeping with her that night, "cause I was.

877
00:44:28,500 --> 00:44:29,490
很有意思 不是吗
It's funny, isn't it, though?

878
00:44:29,636 --> 00:44:32,570
在那场派对上 几个女人走到我跟前
At that party, a couple of women came up to me

879
00:44:32,704 --> 00:44:37,439
指责我对黛安是多么的不好
and started hectoring me about how badly I treated Diane.

880
00:44:37,578 --> 00:44:40,069
『你知道吗 你让她失望透了』
"You really put her down an awful lot, you know. "

881
00:44:40,214 --> 00:44:41,613
我很震惊
I was quite stunned.

882
00:44:41,749 --> 00:44:43,684
之前从没有人...
Nobody before had ever...

883
00:44:45,351 --> 00:44:46,909
在我面前说过这些话
come right out and said that.

884
00:44:47,654 --> 00:44:50,886
我当时陷入了沉思
I think certainly I began to think through this conversation,

885
00:44:51,025 --> 00:44:52,616
『是 她们说的也许是对的』
"Yeah, they're probably right.

886
00:44:52,761 --> 00:44:54,888
『我让她失望了 我是个糟糕透顶的人』
"I am an awful person for putting her down,

887
00:44:55,030 --> 00:44:57,591
『如果她丧失自信』
"and if she lacks confidence,it may well be

888
00:44:57,733 --> 00:45:00,291
『那也许是我以前无意中说的某句话所导致的后果』
"because of some things that I have said in the past. "

889
00:45:00,434 --> 00:45:05,098
我突然想『或许她们知道这件事』
And suddenly I thought,"I wonder if they knew about it. "

890
00:45:05,239 --> 00:45:07,731
黛安可能和她们说过
Diane had probably talked to them about it,

891
00:45:07,876 --> 00:45:09,640
她正考虑离开我
that she was thinking of leaving me,

892
00:45:09,779 --> 00:45:12,247
因为我总在无形中打击着她的自信心
"cause I was not much good for her confidence.

893
00:45:12,381 --> 00:45:15,646
或许她们的话有三分警告的意味
And maybe they were sort of half warning me

894
00:45:15,785 --> 00:45:17,309
想让我明白当时的情形
what was going on.

895
00:45:20,188 --> 00:45:22,316
在她回多伦多之前
Before she went back to Toronto,

896
00:45:23,994 --> 00:45:27,293
我让她带着孩子搬来蒙特利尔
I asked her to move to Montreal and to bring her kids here.

897
00:45:27,431 --> 00:45:29,092
当时的情况很复杂
It was complex and difficult.

898
00:45:29,232 --> 00:45:33,497
她很爱自己的孩子和丈夫
She had this passionate attachment to her kids and to her husband,

899
00:45:33,636 --> 00:45:37,129
但她也很爱我
and she also had this attachment to me,

900
00:45:37,907 --> 00:45:40,673
而我疯狂地爱着她
and I had an attachment which was completely crazy.

901
00:45:40,812 --> 00:45:44,305
我被爱情冲昏了头脑 完全昏了头
I was besotted,just utterly besotted,

902
00:45:44,450 --> 00:45:47,009
而她是那样充满生命里
and she was so full of life,

903
00:45:47,151 --> 00:45:49,711
你只想靠近她
and you just wanted to be there.

904
00:45:49,854 --> 00:45:51,445
只想靠近她
You just wanted to be there.

905
00:45:51,588 --> 00:45:54,057
这种感觉太疯狂了
I mean, it was wild.

906
00:45:54,192 --> 00:45:56,058
你说如果我们真的同居会怎么样？
How it would had been had we been living together,

907
00:45:56,195 --> 00:45:58,390
其实我也不知道
I really have no idea.

908
00:45:58,530 --> 00:46:02,296
你不知道靠得太近的两人可能会...
You don't know what kind of clashes can...

909
00:46:03,036 --> 00:46:04,025
发生怎样的摩擦
can develop,

910
00:46:04,170 --> 00:46:06,329
尽管我怀疑我们或许可以过到一起去
although I suspect that it would have been okay.

911
00:46:06,471 --> 00:46:08,099
我觉得我们应该可以
I know it would have been okay.

912
00:46:13,380 --> 00:46:15,473
我们两个人 我和哈利
Both of us, both Harry and I,

913
00:46:15,615 --> 00:46:18,083
都遇见了一个
met a person who was

914
00:46:20,186 --> 00:46:22,518
厌倦了她当下的生活
bored with her life as it currently was

915
00:46:22,655 --> 00:46:23,986
想要寻求刺激的人
and wanted something more exciting.

916
00:46:25,491 --> 00:46:28,326
她有提起过自己的第一段婚姻么
Did she talk at all about her first marriage?

917
00:46:32,666 --> 00:46:34,258
我不记得太细节的东西了
I don't remember any of the detail,

918
00:46:34,402 --> 00:46:38,565
我知道他们吵架很厉害 日子越来越难挨
except that it was very acrimonious and exceedingly difficult,

919
00:46:38,705 --> 00:46:44,111
失去孩子的抚养权也对她造成了很大打击
and her great distress over losing the kids.

920
00:46:45,180 --> 00:46:46,169
可以讲一下
Can you tell the story

921
00:46:46,314 --> 00:46:48,714
我妈和你爸之间的关系如何吗
of Mom's relationship with your dad?

922
00:46:49,819 --> 00:46:50,808
他们结了婚
They were married,

923
00:46:50,953 --> 00:46:55,116
我不清楚她对他感情有多深
and I don't know how deep her feelings were for him,

924
00:46:55,257 --> 00:46:56,555
但他对她用情很深
but his feelings were deep,

925
00:46:56,692 --> 00:46:59,058
这样的关系让人感觉不适
and it's awful to be in a relationship

926
00:46:59,195 --> 00:47:00,719
因为这个人爱对方的程度
where one person loves the other

927
00:47:00,863 --> 00:47:03,355
远胜过对方爱自己
much more than the other person loves them,

928
00:47:03,500 --> 00:47:04,659
在所有的爱情关系里
and in every relationship,

929
00:47:04,801 --> 00:47:07,099
双方的爱或许都不是对等的
I think one person loves the other person more,

930
00:47:07,236 --> 00:47:09,205
但 幸运的是 这种差距很小
but, hopefully, it's close,

931
00:47:09,339 --> 00:47:12,000
幸运的是 这种差距是会逐渐变化的
and, hopefully, it goes up and down a little bit,

932
00:47:12,810 --> 00:47:14,004
但在我看来
but it seems to me

933
00:47:14,144 --> 00:47:17,546
爱情里永远不存在平等的概念
you never can both equally love each other the same amount.

934
00:47:17,682 --> 00:47:20,548
这个不幸的事实恰好就是生活的真谛
It's unfortunate,but it's just a fact of life.

935
00:47:20,684 --> 00:47:24,212
乔治是妈妈的父母
George was the kind of guy that Mom's parents

936
00:47:24,355 --> 00:47:25,719
会很喜欢的那类人
would have been very happy with.

937
00:47:25,856 --> 00:47:29,122
因为他有钱有事业
He had money,and he had a good job.

938
00:47:29,260 --> 00:47:31,888
我一直觉得她太早嫁给他
So my sense has always been that she married him early,

939
00:47:32,030 --> 00:47:32,928
她嫁给他
and she married him

940
00:47:33,064 --> 00:47:35,727
只是因为他和她门当户对
because he was the kind of person she was supposed to marry.

941
00:47:35,868 --> 00:47:37,892
我觉得我爸对她管得多了一些
I think my dad was really controlling,

942
00:47:38,036 --> 00:47:40,631
而我妈一直很想摆脱这种束缚
and Mom wanted to get out from underneath that.

943
00:47:40,773 --> 00:47:43,504
她不想活在任何人的影子里
She was always trying to get out from under anything

944
00:47:43,643 --> 00:47:45,337
任人摆布
that she felt controlled her

945
00:47:45,478 --> 00:47:48,777
或是替她规划自己的生活
or made her feel like her life was very regulated.

946
00:47:48,914 --> 00:47:50,041
我们都有这样一种共识
We all feel that way.

947
00:47:50,183 --> 00:47:52,013
每到扔垃圾的日子我都有这样一种感觉
I feel that way every garbage day.

948
00:47:52,151 --> 00:47:54,210
每次我需要把垃圾拿出去的时候
Every time I have to take out the garbage,

949
00:47:54,354 --> 00:47:55,821
我就会想『哦 天哪』
it's just like, "Oh, my God. "

950
00:47:55,956 --> 00:47:58,720
这种例行公事会让你觉得生活被强加上了刻度
It makes you realize you're just marking time,

951
00:47:58,859 --> 00:48:00,588
就像是...
and it's just one of those things that...

952
00:48:02,562 --> 00:48:05,429
事实上 现在我都让男朋友倒垃圾
In fact, I make my boyfriend take the garbage out now.

953
00:48:05,565 --> 00:48:06,691
这样我就不用去想这事了
Then I don't have to think about it.

954
00:48:06,833 --> 00:48:08,893
促使她离开
The trigger,the thing that compelled her

955
00:48:09,036 --> 00:48:10,560
第一段婚姻的契机
to leave then and there,

956
00:48:10,705 --> 00:48:13,333
应该是她第一次体会到了爱情的滋味
was that I think she really fell in love,

957
00:48:13,474 --> 00:48:16,444
也许她人生中第一次意识到
and maybe realized for the first time in her life

958
00:48:16,578 --> 00:48:18,704
自己的未来可能是什么样的
what her life could be.

959
00:48:18,846 --> 00:48:20,609
我想这是一种自救
I think she saved herself.

960
00:48:20,748 --> 00:48:23,718
漂流海上的她抓住了一个救生浮标
I think she grabbed on to a life buoy.

961
00:48:23,852 --> 00:48:27,413
这样的决定是为了让自己有勇气生活下去
I think she made a choice to live.

962
00:48:27,556 --> 00:48:29,582
我真的 真的这样觉得
I really, really do.

963
00:48:29,726 --> 00:48:33,320
迈克尔就是那个浮标
And that was with Michael.

964
00:48:33,462 --> 00:48:35,623
她和我爸大吵了一架
She left my dad in the middle of a fight,

965
00:48:35,764 --> 00:48:37,596
把结婚戒指扔到雪地里
threw her wedding ring in the snow,

966
00:48:37,734 --> 00:48:40,668
从家里走了出去 第二天又回来接我们
walked out, and then came back the next day to get us,

967
00:48:40,802 --> 00:48:42,532
我爸把家里的锁全换了
and my dad had changed all the locks.

968
00:48:44,107 --> 00:48:47,134
关于行为不检 我是个现行犯
From misbehavin",I'm in the red

969
00:48:47,845 --> 00:48:50,643
毫不令人意外 我一定没法结婚
Hardly surprising,I'll never be wed

970
00:48:50,781 --> 00:48:55,650
所谓行为不检 不过是算计手段
Instead I'm misbehavin',saving my revenue

971
00:48:55,786 --> 00:48:58,447
最后 乔治得到了孩子的抚养权
Ultimately, George got custody of the kids,

972
00:48:58,588 --> 00:49:02,117
这在六十年代是前所未闻的
and that was unheard of in the '60s,

973
00:49:02,260 --> 00:49:04,229
新闻还上了报纸头版
and it was front-page news.

974
00:49:04,363 --> 00:49:06,727
显然这是加拿大首例
And it was apparently the first time in Canada

975
00:49:06,864 --> 00:49:08,992
女性丧失孩子抚养权的案子
that a woman had ever lost custody of the kids,

976
00:49:09,134 --> 00:49:10,567
因为她和另外一个男人在一起了
and it was because she left for another man,

977
00:49:10,702 --> 00:49:13,499
这不是『端庄女性应有的行为』
and she wasn't "ladylike. "

978
00:49:15,373 --> 00:49:18,832
国家太大 百姓太小
# Ramifications for massive nations

979
00:49:18,978 --> 00:49:22,846
课税一重重 经济跑不动
# Involve taxation and then frustration

980
00:49:22,982 --> 00:49:26,917
我这样诚实的女孩 究竟该怎么办
# What is an honest girl to do?

981
00:49:27,587 --> 00:49:29,020
我是热锅上的蚂蚁
# I'm in a stew

982
00:49:30,590 --> 00:49:34,391
我被迫站街 来平衡赤字
# I walk the streets to balance the sheets

983
00:49:34,528 --> 00:49:38,328
生活重回正轨 阳光却不明媚
# My books are neat and on the beat again

984
00:49:38,465 --> 00:49:42,799
难道行为检点 能抵大堆账单？
# I'm misbehavin' to pay my IOUs

985
00:49:47,175 --> 00:49:48,540
漏了一句词
I missed that line.

986
00:49:56,851 --> 00:50:00,309
我只记得 突然间 母亲就从我们生活中消失了
I remember all of a sudden my mom not being around,

987
00:50:00,455 --> 00:50:03,050
我还记得大人在哭泣
and I can remember adults crying,

988
00:50:03,192 --> 00:50:05,558
我当时不相信大人也是会哭的
and I couldn't believe adults would be crying.

989
00:50:05,694 --> 00:50:08,424
看见我妈双手抱膝 蜷缩着
Seeing my mom with her knees pulled up to her chest,

990
00:50:08,564 --> 00:50:11,056
一个人摇晃着坐在那里
just rocking back and forth.

991
00:50:11,201 --> 00:50:13,756
我有些懵懂地意识到『最糟糕的事已经发生了』
I knew as a child,"The worst thing has happened.

992
00:50:13,901 --> 00:50:17,235
『我不知道是什么事 但这的确是最糟糕的事了』
"I'm not sure what it is,but the worst thing is happening. "

993
00:50:17,373 --> 00:50:19,808
我知道 会有其他人
And I knew that there were other people

994
00:50:19,943 --> 00:50:22,503
来决定我的命运
who were gonna decide what happened to me

995
00:50:22,646 --> 00:50:24,910
和我妈的命运
and what happened to my mom.

996
00:50:25,982 --> 00:50:27,176
对此我无能为力
I had no control.

997
00:50:28,151 --> 00:50:30,642
从没有人问过我们这个问题 如果有人问
We were never asked,"cause had we been asked,

998
00:50:30,787 --> 00:50:32,651
我们肯定会说『我们想和妈妈一起住』
we would have said,"We want to live with our mom. "

999
00:50:32,789 --> 00:50:34,052
我们两个人都会这么说的
For sure, both of us would have.

1000
00:50:34,191 --> 00:50:37,024
那个年纪的孩子所需要的就是这些
At that age, that's what you want.

1001
00:50:37,161 --> 00:50:40,892
我们一个月和妈妈见一次面
We'd have visitation with my mom once a month,

1002
00:50:41,032 --> 00:50:43,194
但我们和老爸一起住
but we lived with my dad,

1003
00:50:43,335 --> 00:50:45,301
也找过两三个人来照顾我们
and there were a couple of caregivers.

1004
00:50:45,435 --> 00:50:50,067
其中有一个是个年纪挺大的女人 她虐待我们
One of them was an older woman
who was physically abusive.

1005
00:50:50,208 --> 00:50:52,176
一个虐待我们的后妈
A successive step-mother who abused us.

1006
00:50:52,311 --> 00:50:54,506
这句话你可以留着 我无所谓
You can keep this in, too. I don't care.

1007
00:50:55,514 --> 00:50:57,415
我记得那时候妈妈开车送我们回家
I remember when Mom used to drive us home,

1008
00:50:57,550 --> 00:50:58,743
她得向我们告别的时候
when she'd say good-bye to us all the time,

1009
00:50:58,884 --> 00:51:00,407
她会一直哭
she would cry and cry.

1010
00:51:00,551 --> 00:51:04,011
很多年以后我们回忆起这些
And I remember years later reminiscing back on that,

1011
00:51:04,157 --> 00:51:06,489
想起她不住地哭泣 我们也会哭
how she would cry and cry, and we'd be crying,

1012
00:51:06,626 --> 00:51:09,288
我们必须告别 进屋去
and we'd have to say good-bye
and go into the house,

1013
00:51:09,429 --> 00:51:11,091
我们不想走
and it was like, we didn't want to leave,

